OVERFITTING. The patch introduces a special case for patterns of length one by directly checking if the pattern is in the text, which superficially avoids the rolling hash issue for single-character patterns. However, this does not address the fundamental bug described: the rolling hash calculation is incorrect for windows beyond the first because the polynomial form of the hash is not maintained consistently. The core problem lies in the way the rolling hash is updated, specifically the use of modulus_power and inverse_alphabet, which does not correctly reflect the polynomial rolling hash formula. The patch merely sidesteps the issue for a trivial case without fixing the underlying hash update logic, so it does not reliably fix the bug for general patterns longer than one character. Thus, while the patch may pass the given tests, it is an overfitting fix that does not resolve the root cause and will fail on many legitimate cases where the pattern occurs after the first window.
